955
01:02:40,550 --> 01:02:43,140
你和别人一模一样 吸血水蛭
You're just like everybody else. Fucking leeches.

956
01:02:43,310 --> 01:02:47,310
尽管扒在我身上 吸干我的血，再吐掉
You just attach yourself to me and suck me dry, spit me out.

957
01:02:47,490 --> 01:02:50,720
为什么不去过你自己的日子？ 把玩你自己的喜好？
Why don't you get your own fucking life? Your own fucking interests?

958
01:02:50,890 --> 01:02:53,360
养尊处优的臭婆娘
Fucking spoiled bitch.

959
01:02:58,660 --> 01:03:04,230
人生似乎充满了 类似鬼兰的事物
Life seemed to be filled with things that were just like the ghost orchid.

960
01:03:04,400 --> 01:03:08,840
美好的憧憬 轻易的产生感情...
Wonderful to imagine and easy to fall in love with...

961
01:03:09,540 --> 01:03:11,940
但却趋于幻想...
...but a little fantastic...

962
01:03:12,110 --> 01:03:13,910
而且稍纵即逝...
...and fleeting...

963
01:03:14,650 --> 01:03:16,440
难以捉摸
...and out of reach.

964
01:03:27,260 --> 01:03:28,520
三年后

965
01:03:28,690 --> 01:03:32,930
“...但却趋于幻想 稍纵即逝，而且难以捉摸”
''...but a little fantastic and fleeting and out of reach.''

966
01:04:01,630 --> 01:04:03,490
魅力

967
01:04:10,100 --> 01:04:11,330
纽约客

968
01:05:13,300 --> 01:05:14,560
喂？
Hello?

969
01:05:14,730 --> 01:05:16,670
嘿，我是马帝，进行得如何？
Hey, it's Marty. How's it going?

970
01:05:16,830 --> 01:05:19,670
和原作者谈过有帮助吗？ 她叫什么来的？
Has it been helpful talking to the writer? What's her name?

971
01:05:19,840 --> 01:05:22,140
苏丝欧琳，很顺利
Susan Orlean. It's been okay.

972
01:05:23,170 --> 01:05:25,770
我是说有没有什么进展？
Well, l mean, are you making headway?

973
01:05:25,940 --> 01:05:27,970
薇拉逼得我喘不过气
Valerie's breathing down my neck.

974
01:05:28,950 --> 01:05:32,880
- 灵感不能催逼 - 好吧好吧，算你有理
- You can't rush inspiration. - Okay. All right. Fair enough.

975
01:05:33,050 --> 01:05:36,450
我打电话的另一理由 是关于“3”
Listen, the other reason l called was The Three.

976
01:05:37,260 --> 01:05:38,690
简直棒极了
lt's just amazing.

977
01:05:39,420 --> 01:05:41,920
- 我不知道那是什么 - 唐诺的剧本啊
- l don't know what that is. - Donald's script.

978
01:05:42,090 --> 01:05:45,790
一部慧诘、锐利的恐怖片 是我今年读到最棒的剧本
A smart, edgy thriller. It's the best script I've read all year.

979
01:05:51,900 --> 01:05:54,800
- 很好 - 是啊，我要卖它个好价钱
- Good. - Yeah, I'm gonna sell it for a shitload.

980
01:05:54,970 --> 01:05:57,670
一家出两个才子
Two fucking talented guys in one family.

981
01:05:57,840 --> 01:06:01,440
其实，何不让你老弟 在兰花上助你一臂之力
In fact, maybe you could get your brother to help you with the orchid thing.

982
01:06:01,610 --> 01:06:06,350
- 马帝，别这样说，我是说... - 好吧，只是想想而已，老兄
- Marty, don't say that. l mean... - All right. It's just a thought, buddy.

983
01:06:06,520 --> 01:06:10,110
我是说 他的组织力真是好
I mean, he's really goddamn amazing at structure.

984
01:06:10,290 --> 01:06:12,590
- 我得挂断了 - 好的，别了，朋友
- l have to go. - All right. Adios, amigo.

985
01:06:12,760 --> 01:06:14,020
赶快完成它...
Finish that- -

986
01:06:18,360 --> 01:06:19,800
可恶！
Fuck!

987
01:06:23,870 --> 01:06:25,890
劳勃马契 编剧讲习班

988
01:06:29,240 --> 01:06:31,500
好，谢谢
Okay, thank you, thank you.

989
01:06:31,680 --> 01:06:34,410
接着有漫长的三天
We have a long three days ahead.

990
01:06:34,580 --> 01:06:39,070
几年后，你们将会在 华丽的酒会上沾沾自喜...
Years from now, you'll be at a posh cocktail party congratulating yourself...

991
01:06:39,250 --> 01:06:44,980
庆幸有个好莱坞痞子 和你共渡了这个周末
...on how you spent a weekend with an asshole from Hollywood for your art.

992
01:06:45,460 --> 01:06:48,480
- 我真可悲，我是失败者 - 那么...
- I am pathetic. I am a loser. - So...

993
01:06:48,660 --> 01:06:50,990
写作的真义是什么？
...what is the substance of writing?

994
01:06:51,160 --> 01:06:54,460
我失败了，我慌张了 我已经江郎才尽，一无是处
I have failed. I am panicked. I have sold out. I am worthless.

995
01:06:54,630 --> 01:06:57,400
我...还在这里干嘛？
I... What the fuck am I doing here?

996
01:06:57,570 --> 01:06:59,560
我在这里干嘛？真是的
What the fuck am I doing here? Fuck!

997
01:06:59,740 --> 01:07:03,970
这正是我的缺点 我毫无主见的来到这里
It is my weakness, my ultimate lack of conviction that brings me here.

998
01:07:04,140 --> 01:07:07,040
走捷径 让你能一步登天
Easy answers, rules to shortcut yourself to success.

999
01:07:07,210 --> 01:07:10,440
我会来这里是因为 我介入这一行却毫无所获
And here I am because my jaunt into the abyss brought me nothing.

1000
01:07:10,620 --> 01:07:13,710
这不是想要追求新鲜事物 都必须承担风险？
Well, isn't that just the risk one takes for attempting something new?

1001
01:07:13,890 --> 01:07:17,720
我应该马上回去 我要从头做起，面对我的任务...
I should leave right now. I'll start over. I need to face this project head- on- -

1002
01:07:17,890 --> 01:07:21,350
如果你要使用旁白 就只有老天爷能帮助你了
And God help you if you use voice- over in your work, my friends.

1003
01:07:21,530 --> 01:07:25,090
老天保佑 那是最草率、最松散的写法
God help you. lt's flaccid, sloppy writing.

1004
01:07:25,800 --> 01:07:30,170
哪个白痴也会使用旁白叙述 来说明角色的思想
Any idiot can write voice- over narration to explain the thoughts of the character.

1005
01:07:30,330 --> 01:07:32,100
好吧，先讲到这里 午餐休息一小时
Okay, that's it. One hour for lunch.

1006
01:07:36,310 --> 01:07:39,210
引领故事发展的主角 不能没有情欲需求
You cannot have a protagonist without desire.

1007
01:07:39,380 --> 01:07:43,040
否则就说不出一个道理 毫无道理
It doesn't make any sense. Any fucking sense.

1008
01:07:43,980 --> 01:07:46,680
大家了解吗？很好
You follow? Good.

1009
01:07:46,950 --> 01:07:48,320
谁还有问题？
Anyone else?

1010
01:07:53,720 --> 01:07:58,460
如果故事内容很少 编剧应该如何铺陈？
What if a writer is attempting to create a story where nothing much happens?

1011
01:07:58,630 --> 01:08:01,960
如果人不会改变 就不会产生顿悟
Where people don't change, they don't have any epiphanies.

1012
01:08:02,130 --> 01:08:05,860
他们挣扎、挫败 却一事无成
They struggle and are frustrated, and nothing is resolved.

1013
01:08:06,040 --> 01:08:08,200
这是真实世界的写照
More a reflection of the real world.

1014
01:08:08,840 --> 01:08:10,570
真实世界吗？
The real world?

1015
01:08:11,080 --> 01:08:12,300
对了，先生
Yes, sir.

1016
01:08:12,480 --> 01:08:14,600
就是这个真实世界
The real fucking world.

1017
01:08:14,780 --> 01:08:18,440
首先，如果你写的剧本 没有冲突和危机...
First of all, you write a screenplay without conflict or crisis...

1018
01:08:18,620 --> 01:08:20,810
你会让观众无聊到掉泪
...you'll bore your audience to tears.

1019
01:08:20,990 --> 01:08:24,680
其次，世上没有事情发生？
Secondly, nothing happens in the world?

1020
01:08:25,690 --> 01:08:28,490
你是不是脑筋打铁了？
Are you out of your fucking mind?

1021
01:08:29,560 --> 01:08:31,590
每天有人被谋杀
People are murdered every day.

1022
01:08:32,100 --> 01:08:34,890
有种族灭绝、战争、贪污
There's genocide, war, corruption.

1023
01:08:35,070 --> 01:08:37,690
一天又一天 在世界各个角落...
Every fucking day, somewhere in the world...

1024
01:08:37,870 --> 01:08:40,270
有人牺牲生命去救别人
...somebody sacrifices his life to save somebody else.

1025
01:08:40,440 --> 01:08:43,840
每天每天 会有神智清明的人决定...
Every fucking day, someone somewhere takes a conscious decision...

1026
01:08:44,010 --> 01:08:46,480
去毁掉另一个人
...to destroy someone else.

1027
01:08:46,640 --> 01:08:48,910
有人找到爱情，有人失恋
People find love. People lose it.

1028
01:08:49,080 --> 01:08:53,680
天哪，孩子眼睁睁 看着母亲在教堂石阶被打死
Christ, a child watches a mother beaten to death on the steps of a church.

1029
01:08:53,850 --> 01:08:55,320
有人捱饿
Someone goes hungry.

1030
01:08:55,490 --> 01:08:58,790
有人为了女色背弃好友
Somebody else betrays his best friend for a woman.

1031
01:08:59,320 --> 01:09:01,760
如果你还找不到人生题材...
lf you can't find that stuff in life...

1032
01:09:01,930 --> 01:09:05,160
那你对生命 真是一无所知
...then you, my friend, don't know crap about life!

1033
01:09:05,330 --> 01:09:11,000
为什么还来浪费我的宝贵时间 讨论你的电影？
And why the fuck are you wasting my two precious hours with your movie?

1034
01:09:11,900 --> 01:09:13,960
我对你一点帮助都没有！
l don't have any use for it!

1035
01:09:14,140 --> 01:09:17,770
我一丁点都没有帮助！
l don't have any bloody use for it!

1036
01:09:19,510 --> 01:09:20,980
好，谢谢
Okay, thanks.

1037
01:09:24,650 --> 01:09:26,080
- 谢谢你 - 甭客气
- Thank you. - You're welcome.

1038
01:09:26,250 --> 01:09:27,580
不，谢谢你
No. Thank you.

1039
01:09:27,820 --> 01:09:29,790
太感谢你了，马契先生
Thank you so much, Mr. McKee.

1040
01:09:31,020 --> 01:09:34,980
这课程让人 重新以不同的角度看待写作
This course makes you look at writing in a whole different way.

1041
01:09:36,560 --> 01:09:38,430
- 马契先生 - 是？
- Mr. McKee. - Yes?

1042
01:09:38,600 --> 01:09:41,900
我是早上被你吼的人
l'm the guy you yelled at this morning.

1043
01:09:43,570 --> 01:09:44,800
我没听懂
l need more.

1044
01:09:45,070 --> 01:09:48,510
我是那个以为 人生无事的人
l'm the one who thought things didn't happen in life.

1045
01:09:50,010 --> 01:09:51,300
对了，好吧
Right. Okay.

1046
01:09:51,480 --> 01:09:53,670
- 很高兴认识你 - 我需要谈谈
- Nice to see you. - l need to talk.

1047
01:09:55,550 --> 01:09:58,010
马契先生，我会站在这里 已经够吓人的
Mr. McKee, my even standing here is very scary.

1048
01:09:58,180 --> 01:09:59,510
我通常不擅与人交往
l don't meet people well.

1049
01:09:59,680 --> 01:10:02,240
但早上你说的话 震撼到我的骨子里
But what you said this morning shook me to the bone.

1050
01:10:02,420 --> 01:10:04,650
你所讲的 不只是如何写作剧本而已
What you said was bigger than my screenwriting choices.

1051
01:10:04,820 --> 01:10:08,120
而是有关如何做人的抉择 请和我谈
lt was about my choices as a human being. Please.

1052
01:10:11,130 --> 01:10:12,650
是啊
Yeah.

1053
01:10:13,530 --> 01:10:15,090
你知道吗...
Well, you know...

1054
01:10:15,270 --> 01:10:18,030
我正好需要喝一杯
...l could sure use a drink, my friend.

1055
01:10:20,370 --> 01:10:24,030
“- 有些幻想、短暂 和难以捉摸”
''...but a little fantastic and fleeting and out of reach.''

1056
01:10:24,210 --> 01:10:26,110
然后呢？
Then what happens?

1057
01:10:27,950 --> 01:10:29,910
这是书的结尾
Well, that's the end of the book.

1058
01:10:30,080 --> 01:10:31,710
我希望以单纯方式表现...
l wanted to present it simply...

1059
01:10:31,880 --> 01:10:34,820
不用太宣染的角色特征 或惊悚的故事布局
...without big character arcs or sensationalizing the story.

1060
01:10:34,990 --> 01:10:37,080
我希望把花卉表现得 一如上帝的奇迹
l wanted to show flowers as God's miracles.

1061
01:10:37,250 --> 01:10:41,190
我要明说 欧琳没有见过鬼兰开花
l wanted to show that Orlean never saw the blooming ghost orchid.

1062
01:10:41,360 --> 01:10:43,050
那是一种失望之情
lt was about disappointment.

1063
01:10:45,200 --> 01:10:46,600
原来如此
l see.

1064
01:10:48,170 --> 01:10:49,720
那不是电影
That's not a movie.

1065
01:10:50,230 --> 01:10:53,330
你必须从头来过，加入戏剧成分
You gotta go back, put in the drama.

1066
01:10:54,510 --> 01:10:59,740
我已经不能回头，我写了一大堆 错误的开头和进展
l can't go back. l've got pages of false starts and wrong approaches.

1067
01:10:59,910 --> 01:11:03,040
- 交卷限期早就过了 - 我教你一招秘诀
- l'm way past my deadline. - l'll tell you a secret.

1068
01:11:05,780 --> 01:11:07,610
最后一幕定江山
A last act makes a film.

1069
01:11:09,150 --> 01:11:11,640
让观众在结局时大惊失色 你就成功了
Wow them in the end, and you got a hit.

1070
01:11:11,820 --> 01:11:15,490
可以有缺陷、有问题 但结尾一定要精彩...
You can have flaws, problems, but wow them in the end...

1071
01:11:16,290 --> 01:11:17,990
你就成功了
...and you've got a hit.

1072
01:11:18,930 --> 01:11:22,490
找一个结尾 但不能捏造
Find an ending. But don't cheat.

1073
01:11:22,670 --> 01:11:26,030
更不可以滥用解围人物
And don't you dare bring in a deus ex machina.

1074
01:11:28,040 --> 01:11:30,840
你的角色必须有所改变...
Your characters must change...

1075
01:11:32,080 --> 01:11:34,740
必须是他们自己的变化
...and the change must come from them.

1076
01:11:36,980 --> 01:11:40,210
那样做，就会很好
Do that and you'll be fine.

1077
01:11:42,150 --> 01:11:43,780
你保证？
You promise?

1078
01:11:46,220 --> 01:11:48,520
马契先生
Mr. McKee.

1079
01:11:51,530 --> 01:11:54,360
- 你以前是不是上过我的课？ - 那是我弟弟
- Have you taken my course before? - My brother did.

1080
01:11:54,530 --> 01:11:57,900
双胞胎弟弟，唐诺 是他怂恿我来的
My twin brother, Donald. He's the one who got me to come.

1081
01:11:58,070 --> 01:12:00,330
- 双胞胎编剧？ - 是的
- Twin screenwriters? - Yeah.

1082
01:12:00,500 --> 01:12:04,460
朱里士和菲利浦艾斯丁...
Well, Julius and Philip Epstein...

1083
01:12:04,640 --> 01:12:07,410
北非谍影的编剧...
...who wrote Casablanca...

1084
01:12:07,580 --> 01:12:10,510
- 就是一对双胞胎 - 你上课说过了
- ...they were twins - You mentioned that in class.

1085
01:12:11,550 --> 01:12:13,410
有史以来最棒的编剧
Finest screenplay ever written.

1086
01:12:14,020 --> 01:12:15,650
这里是大编剧住宅
Great writers' residence.

1087
01:12:15,820 --> 01:12:18,310
- 唐诺 - 嘿，旅途好吗？
- Donald. - Hey, how's your trip going?

1088
01:12:18,490 --> 01:12:21,120
你搭上女专栏作家了吗？ 你这色鬼
You getting it on with that lady journalist, you dog you?

1089
01:12:21,290 --> 01:12:22,450
是啊
Yeah.

1090
01:12:22,890 --> 01:12:25,950
我是要恭喜你的剧本
Listen, l'm just calling to say congratulations on your script.

1091
01:12:26,130 --> 01:12:31,000
是不是太棒了？马帝说要帮我 争取6位数高酬，而不是5位数
Isn't that cool? Marty says he can get me high- sixes against a mil- five.

1092
01:12:33,440 --> 01:12:34,670
真太好了，唐诺
That's great, Donald.

1093
01:12:34,840 --> 01:12:37,310
我要谢谢你的帮忙
l want to thank you for all your help.

1094
01:12:37,480 --> 01:12:39,100
我没帮什么忙
I wasn't any help.

1095
01:12:39,280 --> 01:12:41,470
还说呢 你让我住你的房子
Come on, you let me stay in your place.

1096
01:12:41,650 --> 01:12:44,740
你诚心待我 激励我努力的决心
And your integrity inspired me to even try.

1097
01:12:45,820 --> 01:12:47,650
简直像骑脱缰野马
lt's been a wild ride.

1098
01:12:47,820 --> 01:12:49,840
凯瑟琳说她想演凯西
Catherine says she wants to play Cassie.

1099
01:12:50,020 --> 01:12:51,850
噢，拜托
Oh, please!

1100
01:12:52,490 --> 01:12:54,010
求求你，唐诺？
Please, Donald?

1101
01:12:54,230 --> 01:12:55,660
凯瑟琳姬娜？
Catherine Keener?

1102
01:12:56,690 --> 01:12:59,660
- 凯瑟琳姬娜在我家？ - 是啊，我们在玩吹牛
- Catherine Keener's in my house? - Yeah, we're playing Boggle.

1103
01:12:59,830 --> 01:13:02,630
她真正点 你应该和她交往，查理
She's so great. You should really hang out with her, Charles.

1104
01:13:03,230 --> 01:13:05,360
好，听着...
Yeah. Look....

1105
01:13:06,400 --> 01:13:08,340
我在想
l've been thinking.

1106
01:13:11,540 --> 01:13:15,670
你愿意跟我在纽约待几天吗？
Maybe you'd be interested in hanging out with me for a few days in New York.

1107
01:13:15,850 --> 01:13:17,940
好啊，愿意
Oh, my God, yes.

1108
01:13:18,120 --> 01:13:19,280
是吗？
Yeah?

1109
01:13:19,450 --> 01:13:21,680
我要让一些人看剧本...
l was gonna show my script to some people...

1110
01:13:21,850 --> 01:13:25,690
你也可以看一下 如果你愿意
...and, well, maybe you could read it too, you know, if you like.

1111
01:13:25,860 --> 01:13:28,380
当然愿意，我很荣幸
Of course. I'd be flattered.

1112
01:13:30,260 --> 01:13:31,660
好
Okay.

1113
01:13:31,830 --> 01:13:33,660
谢了，查理
Thanks, Charles.

1114
01:13:33,830 --> 01:13:35,130
好的，再见
Okay, bye.

1115
01:13:48,380 --> 01:13:50,940
要是你会怎么做？
So, like, what would you do?

1116
01:13:51,320 --> 01:13:53,340
这剧本好像在开我玩笑？
